Rating: 4
Almost gave only 3 forks, but then I remembered my crazy carvings for these potatoes that won't go away! The mustardy, garlicky, bite with the creamy almost sweet reds is heavenly. I might use a little extra dressing for these. Just don't over boil the potatoes or they may start to fall apart on you. I didn't even bother with the skewers last time and just tossed them in a pan under the broiler. I won't lie- I even ate a 1/4 of them before they even made it to the broiler - raw garlic and all. A few splashes of white wine vinegar added an extra punch too - any dried herb can substitute for the fresh thyme as well if need be. Yum!! I might even have a few extra babies to make as a little snack right now!

