Rating: 3
This was tasty and simple. I soaked the skewers for about 30 minutes to keep them from burning. I used both red and white fingerling potatoes fresh from the farmer's market for a little extra interest. Someone mentioned that this was bland-I suggest tasting the marinade before adding the potatoes and adjusting it to suit your individual liking-for me that means more garlic!! Also, someone mentioned that the potatoes were mushy and difficult to skewer. Make sure you don't cook them completely when you boil them-that may have been the problem. When I drained these, they were still "al dente".

